snippet: The federally run health insurance exchange opened in Ohio on Tuesday, but the state had no certified “navigators” to help consumers find insurance plans on the first day of the Affordable Care Act marketplace.
abstract: The federally run health insurance exchange opened in Ohio on Tuesday, but the state had no certified “navigators” to help consumers find insurance plans on the first day of the Affordable Care Act marketplace.

headline.main: In Ohio, Little Help for Consumers in Navigating Enrollment
